        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 7:59PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 759 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Deer Park, or 6 miles north of Citronelle, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Citronelle, Gulfcrest, Deer Park, Mount Vernon, and Movico.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
